subSubSection.paragraph:
Pereopod-2 (Fig. 
5B
): similar to pereopod-1, except basis and propodus longer. Propodus with ventrodistal pectinate small seta. Dactylus and unguis shorter than propodus.

Pereopod-5 (Fig. 
5E
): Similar to pereopod-4, except carpus and dactylus longer. Basis with setulose seta on mid-ventral margin.

Pleopods: Absent. (Fig. 
7B
